### =====================================
### Multiple Instance Cache Tests
### =====================================
### These tests demonstrate the multiple instances feature for the Caching service.
### Instance-specific endpoints allow using named cache instances to isolate data.
###

###
### Named Instance: cache1
### PUT - Store data in named cache instance 'cache1'
POST {{baseUrl}}/services/caching/api/cache1/put/user-profile-1
Content-Type: application/json
x-api-key: {{apiKey}}

{
    "userId": "1",
    "name": "Alice",
    "role": "admin",
    "createdAt": "{{$datetime iso8601}}"
}

###

### Named Instance: cache1
### GET - Retrieve data from cache instance 'cache1'
GET {{baseUrl}}/services/caching/api/cache1/get/user-profile-1
